Three people were killed in inter-clan clashes in Lagdera, Garissa, on Thursday. Residents said Burale Dekow, Mohamed Farah and Abdi Derow died of gunshots wounds. They were buried in Modogashe according to Islamic rites. Three other people were injured and are admitted to Modogashe Hospital. Residents said they were attacked while herding camels. Local leaders want answers over a protracted border feud with Isiolo. Lagdera MP Mohamed Hire (pictured) and former Woman Representative Shukran Gure accused some leaders of inciting residents.